cy handling**\\\\n\\\\nAlright, I’m considering the legacy setup where no trigger results in null with the two-argument form. This gives fallback coverage. I also see that the ContextFinderTest loadsThreeArg is already triggering, which might be a potential issue since cleanProperties removes JAXB_CONTEXT_FACTORY before passing it along. So, I need to keep an eye on that trigger to ensure everything functions smoothly. It seems good overall!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_zH38UPYJmUpTHxWGa2tWmME6|fc_0cd2afb14a04b5a30169f70317d63481a19326fc4bb17bbf5a\", \"name\": \"write\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/jakarta.xml.bind/jakarta.xml.bind-api/4.1.0-M1/src/test/java/org/glassfish/jaxb/runtime/v2/ContextFactory.java\", \"content\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org.glassfish.jaxb.runtime.v2;\\n\\nimport java.util.Map;\\n\\nimport jakarta.xml.bind.JAXBContext;\\nimport jakarta.xml.bind.JAXBContextFactory;\\nimport jakarta.xml.bind.JAXBException;\\nimport jakarta_xml_bind.jakarta_xml_bind_api.classproperties.PropertiesBoundType;\\nimport jakarta_xml_bind.jakarta_xml_bind_api.factorybacked.FactoryBackedBoundType;\\nimport jakarta_xml_bind.jakarta_xml_bind_api.support.StubJaxbContext;\\n\\npublic class ContextFactory implements JAXBContextFactory {\\n    @Override\\n    public JAXBContext createContext(Class<?>[] classesToBeBound, Map<String, ?> properties) throws JAXBException {\\n        if (containsClass(classesToBeBound, FactoryBackedBoundType.class)) {\\n            return new StubJaxbContext(\\\"factory-backed-classes-factory\\\");\\n        }\\n        if (containsClass(classesToBeBound, PropertiesBoundType.class)) {\\n            return new StubJaxbContext(\\\"properties-classes-factory\\\");\\n        }\\n        throw new JAXBException(\\\"Unsupp